subSubSection.paragraph:
Male not seen. Female paired first pleopods 2 ­segmented. Brood pouch large, almost fan­shaped, margins weakly scalloped, with marginal long setae. Tergal thickenings above acetabula of pleopods 2–4 with fringe of long, moderately dense setae. Eggs large, diameter 1.2 mm (
Alcock , 1905
).
